---
description: Inertia React pages — data flow, Ant Design, API calls
globs: resources/js/**/*.js,resources/js/**/*.jsx
alwaysApply: false
---

# Data from server

- Page props come from `usePage().props` (Inertia); do not invent props — align with the Laravel controller.

# Navigation & URLs

- Use Inertia router (`Inertia.get` / `Inertia.post` / `<Link>`) for same-app navigation where the codebase does; use `axios` only where the project already does for JSON endpoints.

# UI

- Prefer Ant Design components for tables, forms, and modals to match existing screens.
- Keep layout consistent with `Layout` and existing page patterns (e.g. Helmet for title).

# State

- Prefer local `useState` / small hooks following neighboring code; avoid introducing new global state libraries without approval.

# Naming

- Follow existing naming even if imperfect (e.g. legacy typos in state names) unless the task is explicitly to rename.
